</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1438,261,1407]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,320,1269,1295]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Remarks.</emphasis>
A smaller dark castaneous species with violaceous lustre. Differing from congeners by the overall dark coloration and erect dorsal pubescence. Further differs from the variant of 
<taxonomicName authority="Heller" authorityName="Heller" box="[1196,1436,1306,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subsericea">
<emphasis box="[1196,1354,1307,1332]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">T. subsericea</emphasis>
Heller
</taxonomicName>
with pustulate discal elytral interspaces by having the elytral apex evenly and convexly narrowed. Unique male. The name commemorates a satellite of planet 
<taxonomicName box="[762,826,1381,1407]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mars" status="n. sp.">Mars</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
